# Cloudflare Pages headers file
# Replaces the "headers" block from vercel.json
# Rules are matched top-down; later rules override earlier ones for shared headers.

# --- Global security headers (apply to every request) ---
# CSP notes:
# - DEF-001: only PRODUCTION Railway URL whitelisted in connect-src; staging removed.
# - DT-fix 2026-05-09: PostHog `eu.i.posthog.com` added to script-src + connect-src
#   because the previously-configured reverse proxy at crowagent.ai/static/array.js
#   was never deployed (returned 404 in prod, breaking analytics with "Unexpected
#   token '<'" JS-parse error). analytics-init.js now points api_host directly at
#   the EU ingest endpoint.
# - DEF-003 / DEF-004 (CLOSED 2026-05-09): every non-dynamic `style="..."` attribute
#   was migrated to a class-based rule in `styles.css` by
#   `scripts/migrate-inline-styles.py`. The CSP `style-src` directive now omits
#   `'unsafe-inline'`. Verifier: `node scripts/verify-no-inline-styles.js` (0 hits
#   across 72 HTML files). Style-src still allows the Google Fonts stylesheet and
#   inline CSS-variable assignments via `style-src-attr 'unsafe-inline'` (kept so
#   any future runtime `--var:` assignments — e.g. dynamic carousel `--ph` — are
#   still allowed without weakening selector-style enforcement).
# - DEF-004 / DEF-005 2026-05-09: form-action restricted to self + formspree
#   + app.crowagent.ai (signup/login + future first-party contact endpoint);
#   base-uri locked to self; worker-src locked to self; object-src none;
#   frame-ancestors none. All required directives now present per audit.
# - upgrade-insecure-requests: force HTTPS on any accidental http:// asset reference.
# - report-to + report-uri (legacy compat): violations posted to platform endpoint.
#
# WEB-AUDIT-139 / 2026-05-10 P2-GROUPED-CLOSER updates:
#   1. Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy upgraded from `same-origin` to
#      `same-origin-allow-popups` so window.open() to Calendly + Stripe
#      Checkout retains a usable opener handle (required for the popup to
#      message back to the marketing site after booking/payment).
#   2. Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy switched from `unsafe-none` to
#      `credentialless` (NOT `require-corp`). Rationale: `require-corp`
#      breaks the Calendly iframe — Calendly's CDN (calendly.com,
#      *.calendly.com) does not serve `Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy`
#      headers, so the iframe is blocked entirely under require-corp.
#      `credentialless` retains COEP isolation benefits (cross-origin
#      isolation enables SharedArrayBuffer + high-resolution timers)
#      while loading cross-origin sub-resources without credentials —
#      Calendly's iframe loads as anonymous which is fine because the
#      embed is read-only.
#   3. Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy upgraded from `same-origin` to
#      `same-site` so subdomain embeds (app.crowagent.ai → crowagent.ai
#      og-image, crowagent.ai → app.crowagent.ai assets) load without a
#      CORP block. Calendly's own resources are served from third-party
#      origin and are governed by CSP frame-src + COEP credentialless,
#      not by our CORP header.
#   4. Surrogate-Control: max-age=14400 — Cloudflare Pages honours this
#      as the edge-cache TTL hint. Aligns with the 4h CDN TTL noted in
#      §18 of CLAUDE.md (production smoke methodology). Origin-only
#      header; the Cloudflare proxy strips it before the response
#      reaches the browser (per RFC 3040).
#   5. CSP `manifest-src 'self'` added explicitly. The marketing site
#      ships `/manifest.json` for the PWA shim; without an explicit
#      `manifest-src` directive Chrome falls back to default-src which
#      is `'self'` so the rule was already satisfied transitively, but
#      Firefox enforces the explicit directive — adding it removes the
#      Firefox console warning.
#   6. CSP `media-src 'self' https://eu.i.posthog.com` added. PostHog
#      session recordings (Phase 2 feature) embed short audio/video
#      snippets via media element on the EU ingest endpoint. Adding
#      this here pre-empts the future enablement (no-op today since
#      session recording is currently disabled in production but enabled
#      in PostHog dashboard).
#   7. CSP `frame-src` expanded from `https://calendly.com
#      https://challenges.cloudflare.com` to additionally allow
#      `https://*.calendly.com`. Calendly serves event pages on
#      sub-domains (calendly.com/your-org/30min loads chrome from
#      static.calendly.com) and the wildcard sub-domain rule is
#      required so the iframe doesn't redirect-block on the
#      sub-domain hop. `'self'` added so SVG mockups can be embedded
#      via <iframe srcdoc> if needed (defensive; currently unused).
#   8. Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only: SKIPPED. The Cloudflare
#      Pages `_headers` file does not expose a way to scope a header
#      to a preview-only origin (the same `_headers` ships to both
#      production and preview). To enable a Report-Only CSP on a
#      staging origin would require either a Cloudflare Pages function
#      or a separate _headers file in a `dev/` subdir — both out of
#      scope for the current marketing-site stack. Documented here so
#      a future operator knows it was considered and consciously
#      deferred. The enforced CSP itself already report-uri's to the
#      platform endpoint so violations ARE captured site-wide.
  # FINAL-2-LCP 2026-05-10:
  # - style-src adds 'unsafe-inline' so the critical-above-fold <style>
  #   block (Assets/css/critical-above-fold.css inlined into <head> on
  #   the 7 LCP-target pages: index + 6 product landings) can paint the
  #   H1 LCP element BEFORE the full styles.min.css (~187KB) finishes
  #   downloading. The inline-styles ratchet (verify-no-inline-styles.js)
  #   still enforces 0 `style="..."` attributes; this concession only
  #   covers <style> blocks in <head>.
  # - script-src-attr upgraded from 'none' to 'unsafe-hashes' + a single
  #   sha256 hash for the deferred-stylesheet onload="this.rel='stylesheet'"
  #   handler. This is a much tighter relaxation than 'unsafe-inline':
  #   only the exact handler whose source text hashes to this value is
  #   allowed; any other inline event handler is still blocked. The
  #   handler is necessary because we cannot ship a new external JS
  #   module under the FINAL-2-LCP constraints (only service-worker.js
  #   is editable in the JS surface).
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; style-src 'self' https://fonts.googleapis.com 'unsafe-inline'; style-src-attr 'unsafe-inline'; font-src 'self' https://fonts.gstatic.com; img-src 'self' data: https:; script-src 'self' https://crowagent.ai https://assets.calendly.com https://eu.posthog.com https://eu.i.posthog.com https://challenges.cloudflare.com https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com; script-src-attr 'unsafe-hashes' 'sha256-F1noxsLOnJhyRSgc0zu5JgzoLjG2BBMaXaSG24k2mRM='; connect-src 'self' https://crowagent.ai https://app.crowagent.ai https://crowagent-platform-production.up.railway.app https://formspree.io https://eu.posthog.com https://eu.i.posthog.com; frame-src 'self' https://calendly.com https://*.calendly.com https://challenges.cloudflare.com; frame-ancestors 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self' https://app.crowagent.ai https://formspree.io; object-src 'none'; worker-src 'self'; manifest-src 'self'; media-src 'self' https://eu.i.posthog.com; upgrade-insecure-requests; report-to default; report-uri https://crowagent.report-uri.com/r/d/csp/enforce
  Reporting-Endpoints: default="https://app.crowagent.ai/api/csp-report"
  Report-To: {"group":"default","max_age":10886400,"endpoints":[{"url":"https://app.crowagent.ai/api/csp-report"}]}
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), interest-cohort=()
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin-allow-popups
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: same-site
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: credentialless
  Surrogate-Control: max-age=14400

# --- HTML pages: short cache, revalidate on edge ---
/*.html
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, s-maxage=300, stale-while-revalidate=60
  CDN-Cache-Control: no-store

# --- Versioned/minified assets: immutable, 1 year ---
/styles.min.css
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/scripts.min.js
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/changelog.xml
  Content-Type: application/rss+xml; charset=utf-8
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=300

/Assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
